{{nihongo|'''Yuito Suzuki'''|鈴木 唯人|Suzuki Yuito|born 25 October 2001}} is a Japanese professional [[association football|footballer]] who plays as an [[attacking midfielder]] or a [[winger (association football)|winger]] for German {{German football updater|SCFreibu}} club [[SC Freiburg]] and the [[Japan national football team|Japan national team]].

==Club career==
===Shimizu S-Pulse===
After graduating from Ichiritsu Funabashi High School in 2019, Suzuki began his professional career with [[Shimizu S-Pulse]], joining the club ahead of the 2020 season.

====Loan to Strasbourg====
On 28 January 2023, Suzuki moved abroad to France and officially joined [[Ligue 1]] club [[RC Strasbourg Alsace]] on loan for 2022–23 season.<ref>{{cite web|publisher=Strasbourg|url=https://www.rcstrasbourgalsace.fr/yuito-suzuki-au-racing/|title=YUITO SUZUKI AU RACING|date=28 January 2023|access-date=3 February 2023|language=fr}}</ref>

===Brøndby===
Suzuki moved to [[Danish Superliga]] club [[Brøndby IF|Brøndby]] on 12 August 2023, signing a four-year contract.<ref>{{cite web |title=Brøndby IF henter japanske Yuito Suzuki |url=https://brondby.com/nyheder/klub/2023/august/brondby-if-henter-japanske-yuito-suzuki |website=Brøndby IF |access-date=29 August 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230814043715/https://brondby.com/nyheder/klub/2023/august/brondby-if-henter-japanske-yuito-suzuki |archive-date=14 August 2023 |language=da |date=12 August 2023}}</ref> He made his debut for the club on 28 August, replacing [[Mathias Kvistgaarden]] in the 67th minute of a 1–0 [[2023–24 Danish Superliga|league]] victory away against [[Vejle Boldklub]].<ref>{{cite news |last1=Bak |first1=Daniel |title=Brøndby har flere mulige debutanter med til Vejle |url=https://bold.dk/fodbold/stillinger/superligaen/nyheder/brondby-har-flere-mulige-debutanter-med-til-vejle |access-date=29 August 2023 |work=bold.dk |date=28 August 2023 |language=da}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=Vejle BK – Brøndby IF 0:1 (Superligaen 2023/2024, 6. Round) |url=https://www.worldfootball.net/match-report/ma9629264/lineup/ |website=WorldFootball.net |publisher=HEIM:SPIEL |access-date=29 August 2023}}</ref> On 27 September, he scored his first goal for the club in a 3–0 [[2023–24 Danish Cup|Danish Cup]] win over [[Hellerup IK|HIK]].<ref>{{cite news |title=Hårdt for HIK-keeper: Brøndby kørte rundt med ham |url=https://www.tipsbladet.dk/nyhed/superliga/broendby-udnytter-hik-keepers-gavebod-i-sikker-pokalsejr |access-date=27 September 2023 |work=Tipsbladet |date=27 September 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230927201032/https://www.tipsbladet.dk/nyhed/superliga/broendby-udnytter-hik-keepers-gavebod-i-sikker-pokalsejr |archive-date=27 September 2023 |language=da}}</ref> His first league goal followed four days later, on 1 October, contributing to a 3–0 away victory against [[Hvidovre IF|Hvidovre]].<ref>{{cite news |last1=Leerberg |first1=Mathias |last2=Nelausen |first2=Raymund |title=Suzuki er godt kørende i BIF: Et troværdigt alternativ |url=https://bold.dk/fodbold/klubber/broendby-if/nyheder/suzuki-er-godt-korende-i-bif-et-trovaerdigt-alternativ |access-date=2 October 2023 |work=bold.dk |date=2 October 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231002120110/https://bold.dk/fodbold/klubber/broendby-if/nyheder/suzuki-er-godt-korende-i-bif-et-trovaerdigt-alternativ |archive-date=2 October 2023 |language=da}}</ref> On 17 March 2024, Suzuki scored his first [[hat-trick (association football)|hat-trick]], helping Brøndby to a 4–1 league win over [[Silkeborg IF|Silkeborg]].<ref>{{cite news |title=Silkeborg fik tæsk i Brøndby, men kunne alligevel juble |url=https://politiken.dk/sport/fodbold/art9816702/Silkeborg-fik-t%C3%A6sk-i-Br%C3%B8ndby-men-kunne-alligevel-juble |access-date=17 March 2024 |work=Politiken |date=17 March 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240317213520/https://politiken.dk/sport/fodbold/art9816702/Silkeborg-fik-t%C3%A6sk-i-Br%C3%B8ndby-men-kunne-alligevel-juble |archive-date=17 March 2024 |language=da-DK}}</ref> Throughout the season, he scored nine goals and eight assists for the club in the league, as well as two goals and two assists in the Danish Cup.<ref>{{Cite web |date=26 May 2024 |title=ブレンビーが最終節で痛恨の敗戦、2位転落で優勝逃す...鈴木唯人は今季リーグ戦で9G8Aを記録 |url=https://web.gekisaka.jp/news/world/detail/?408074-408074-fl |access-date=26 May 2024 |website=ゲキサカ |language=ja}}</ref>

===SC Freiburg===
On 20 May 2025, it was announced that Suzuki would join German [[Bundesliga]] club [[SC Freiburg]], with the transfer becoming effective on 1 July 2025.<ref>{{cite web |title=Yuito Suzuki skifter til SC Freiburg efter sæsonen |url=https://brondby.com/nyheder/herrer/2025/maj/yuito-suzuki-skifter-til-sc-freiburg-efter-saesonen |website=Brøndby IF |access-date=26 May 2025 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20250526203224/https://brondby.com/nyheder/herrer/2025/maj/yuito-suzuki-skifter-til-sc-freiburg-efter-saesonen |archive-date=26 May 2025 |language=da |date=20 May 2025}}</ref> The terms of the agreement were not officially disclosed, though ''[[Kicker (magazine)|kicker]]'' reported the base transfer fee to be €8 million.<ref>{{cite news |title="Besondere Mischung": Freiburg verpflichtet Suzuki |url=https://www.kicker.de/besondere-mischung-freiburg-verpflichtet-suzuki-1120387/artikel |access-date=26 May 2025 |work=[[kicker (magazine)|kicker]] |date=20 May 2025 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20250526204248/https://www.kicker.de/besondere-mischung-freiburg-verpflichtet-suzuki-1120387/artikel |archive-date=26 May 2025 |language=de-DE}}</ref> In a statement announcing the signing, Freiburg board member Jochen Saier described Suzuki as "a player who can both score goals and set up his teammates," adding: "His pace, flexibility and technique will improve our overall attacking play as a team."<ref>{{cite web |title=Yuito Suzuki signs for SC Freiburg |url=https://www.scfreiburg.com/en/latest/news/first-team/2024-25/yuito-suzuki-signs-for-sc-freiburg/ |website=SC Freiburg |access-date=26 May 2025 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20250526203829/https://www.scfreiburg.com/en/latest/news/first-team/2024-25/yuito-suzuki-signs-for-sc-freiburg/ |archive-date=26 May 2025 |date=20 May 2025}}</ref>

Suzuki made his competitive debut for Freiburg on 16 August 2025, coming on for [[Patrick Osterhage]] in the 62nd minute of a 2–0 [[DFB-Pokal]] first-round win away to [[Sportfreunde Lotte]] at the [[Stadion am Lotter Kreuz]].<ref>{{cite news |title=Dinkci eröffnet satt per Volley: Freiburg in der zweiten Runde |url=https://www.kicker.de/lotte-gegen-freiburg-2025-dfb-pokal-5044209/spielbericht |access-date=12 September 2025 |work=kicker |date=16 August 2025 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20250818165338/https://www.kicker.de/lotte-gegen-freiburg-2025-dfb-pokal-5044209/spielbericht |archive-date=18 August 2025 |language=de-DE |trans-title=Dinkci scores with a crisp volley: Freiburg into the second round}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=Spielstatistik Sportfreunde Lotte – SC Freiburg |url=https://www.ndr.de/sport/ergebnisse/spielstatistik-2264.html |website=NDR |access-date=12 September 2025 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20250912164241/https://www.ndr.de/sport/ergebnisse/spielstatistik-2264.html |archive-date=12 September 2025 |language=de}}</ref> He made his Bundesliga debut a week later, starting on the opening matchday of the [[2025–26 Bundesliga|2025–26 season]] in a 3–1 home defeat to [[FC Augsburg]] at the [[Europa-Park Stadion]], and was substituted after 70 minutes.<ref>{{cite news |title=Augsburg kontert Freiburg aus und feiert gelungenes Wagner-Debüt |url=https://www.kicker.de/freiburg-gegen-augsburg-2025-bundesliga-5050750/analyse |access-date=12 September 2025 |work=kicker |date=23 August 2025 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20250904042551/https://www.kicker.de/freiburg-gegen-augsburg-2025-bundesliga-5050750/analyse |archive-date=4 September 2025 |language=de-DE |trans-title=Augsburg hit Freiburg on the counter and celebrate successful Wagner debut}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last1=Ruf |first1=Christoph |title=Wagners Energiespeicher entleert sich spektakulär |url=https://www.sueddeutsche.de/sport/sandro-wagner-trainer-fc-augsburg-bundesliga-li.3302558 |access-date=12 September 2025 |work=Süddeutsche Zeitung |date=24 August 2025 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20250831090121/https://www.sueddeutsche.de/sport/sandro-wagner-trainer-fc-augsburg-bundesliga-li.3302558 |archive-date=31 August 2025 |language=de |trans-title=Wagner runs out of energy in spectacular fashion}}</ref>

On 23 October 2025, Suzuki scored his first competitive goal for Freiburg, opening the scoring in a 2–0 home win over [[FC Utrecht|Utrecht]] in the [[UEFA Europa League]] group stage.<ref>{{cite web |title=Freiburg – Utrecht 2:0 |url=https://www.soccerway.com/match/freiburg-fiEQZ7C7/utrecht-p6QXMgOj/?mid=ILCxIJ2n |website=Soccerway |publisher=Sportsight s.r.o. |access-date=26 November 2025}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=Dank Grifos feinem Füßchen: Freiburg beendet Remis-Serie gegen Utrecht |url=https://www.kicker.de/freiburg-gegen-utrecht-2025-europa-league-5170490/analyse |access-date=26 November 2025 |work=kicker |date=23 October 2025 |language=de-DE |trans-title=Thanks to Grifo's fine touch: Freiburg end their run of draws against Utrecht}}</ref> His performance was praised by head coach [[Julian Schuster]] who highlighted Suzuki's way of fighting back after recently finding himself on the fringes of the team.<ref>{{cite news |title="Dann hast du zwei Möglichkeiten": Schuster freut sich über Suzukis Entwicklung |url=https://www.kicker.de/dann-hast-du-zwei-moeglichkeiten-schuster-freut-sich-ueber-suzukis-entwicklung-1158696/artikel |access-date=26 November 2025 |work=kicker |date=24 October 2025 |language=de-DE |trans-title="Then you have two options": Schuster pleased with Suzuki's development}}</ref>

On 9 November 2025, Suzuki scored his first Bundesliga goal, his first-time finish setting Freiburg on their way to a 2–1 home win over [[FC St. Pauli]].<ref>{{cite news |title=Suzukis Direktabnahme bringt Freiburgs Heimsieg auf den Weg |url=https://www.kicker.de/freiburg-gegen-st-pauli-2025-bundesliga-5050833/analyse |access-date=26 November 2025 |work=kicker |date=9 November 2025 |language=de |trans-title=Suzuki's first-time finish puts Freiburg on course for a home win}}</ref> In a piece published on 14 November, ''kicker'' described him as a "marathon runner" with a steep learning curve, reporting that a recent omission from the [[Japan national football team|Japan national team]] squad had helped drive his improvement as he added further goals and assists for Freiburg.<ref>{{cite news |title=Steile Lernkurve beim "Marathonläufer": Wie Suzuki eine Enttäuschung half |url=https://www.kicker.de/steile-lernkurve-beim-marathonlaeufer-wie-suzuki-eine-enttaeuschung-half-1165787/artikel |access-date=26 November 2025 |work=kicker |date=14 November 2025 |language=de |trans-title=Steep learning curve for the "marathon runner": How a disappointment helped Suzuki}}</ref> On 22 November, he again opened the scoring, giving Freiburg a 1–0 lead away to [[FC Bayern Munich|Bayern Munich]] before the defending champions came back to win 6–2.<ref>{{cite web |title=Match report: FC Bayern v SC Freiburg |url=https://fcbayern.com/en/matches/profis/bundesliga/2025-2026/fc-bayern-muenchen-sport-club-freiburg-22-11-2025/report |website=FC Bayern Munich |date=22 November 2025 |access-date=26 November 2025}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=Olise überragt: Bayern trotzt dem Freiburger Blitzstart |url=https://www.kicker.de/bayern-gegen-freiburg-2025-bundesliga-5050840/analyse |access-date=26 November 2025 |work=kicker |date=22 November 2025 |language=de |trans-title=Olise shines: Bayern withstand Freiburg's lightning start}}</ref>

==International career==
Suzuki made his debut for the [[Japan national football team|Japan national team]] on 6 June 2024 in a [[2026 FIFA World Cup qualification – AFC second round|2026 FIFA World Cup qualifier]] against [[Myanmar national football team|Myanmar]] at the [[Thuwunna Stadium]]. He substituted [[Ritsu Dōan]] at half-time as Japan won 5–0.<ref>{{cite web|publisher=ESPN|url=https://www.espn.com/soccer/match/_/gameId/687399/|title=Myanmar v Japan game report|date=6 June 2024}}</ref>

